# Rules Index & Precedence

When multiple rules apply, use **topic ownership** below first; if still ambiguous, use precedence.

When rules conflict, apply this hierarchy (highest authority first):

1. `architecture/global-architecture.mdc` ‚Äî SSOT for layers, dependencies, features/entities/shared
2. `architecture/cursor-enforcement.mdc` ‚Äî Pre-flight process (does not override architecture)
3. Layer rules (same tier; more specific path wins):
   - `architecture/ui-architecture.mdc`
   - `architecture/state-and-reactivity.mdc`
   - `architecture/logic-discipline.mdc` ‚Äî extraction discipline, pure-return, and `logic/` placement
   - `architecture/forms.mdc`
   - `nextjs-and-performance.mdc`
4. `architecture/typescript.mdc`
5. `architecture/naming.mdc`
6. `architecture/styling-system.mdc`
7. UX: `ux/accessibility.mdc` > `ux/content.mdc` > `ux/animations.mdc`
8. `docs/**` ‚Äî **non-authoritative**; sync when `global-architecture` changes

